vulnerability.name: USN-6299-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that poppler incorrectly handled certain malformed PDF files. If a user or an automated system were tricked into opening a specially crafted PDF file, a remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause a denial of service. (CVE-2020-36023, CVE-2020-36024)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in poppler.
